COVID-19 Information

COVID-19 is an infectious disease caused by the coronavirus SARS-CoV-2. It primarily spreads through respiratory droplets when an infected person coughs, sneezes, or talks.

Symptoms

  • Fever or chills
  • Cough
  • Shortness of breath or difficulty breathing
  • Fatigue
  • Loss of taste or smell

Risk Factors

Certain groups of people are at higher risk of developing severe illness from COVID-19:

  • Older adults (65+ years)
  • Individuals with underlying medical conditions (e.g., heart disease, diabetes, respiratory conditions)
  • People with weakened immune systems

Prevention

  • Wear a mask in crowded places
  • Maintain social distancing
  • Wash your hands frequently
  • Avoid touching your face
  • Get vaccinated
); }; export default Info;
